snippet.textDisplay: Finally something that befits the level of Coke Studio.. behtareen... the only song from this season after Shikwa Jawab e Shikwa that’s gonna end up in my playlist... love the folk vibes, and especially the folk singer with the ektara type instrument and khartaal.. he has terrific vocal range. Also the flute at the beginning and in the end just melted my heart. At places, this composition sounds so similar to Bengali folk  music (especially the flute parts), which is also very close to my heart. Love from Canada!

snippet.textDisplay:
Mumal Rano is a romantic tale of Momal and Rano from the Sindhi folklore and Rajasthani folklore. It is a multifaceted story that entails adventure, magic, schemes, beauty, love, ordeals of separation and above all romantic tragedy.
The fame of the story is ascribed to Ganj or Shah Jo Risalo; the poetry book Shah Abdul Latif Bhitta.
